The Commission of Inquiry into State Capture will continue to hear testimony by Transnet Governance Executive Manager, Peter Volmink. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Transnet executives previously single-handedly signed multi-billion rand deals. That's according to two witnesses at the state capture inquiry. On Tuesday, board chair Popo Molefe singled out Anoj Singh, Brian Molefe and Siyabonga Gama. He claims they facilitated state capture. READ: Transnet exec in state capture inquiry hot seat On Thursday, executive manager Peter Volmink testified that Transnet leaders broke rules to cut deals. He claims executives purposefully broke the rules.
Volmink returns to the stand on Friday.